    <section address="Attributes">
      <title>Attributes</title>
      <content>
        <para>
          <legacyItalic>Section attributes</legacyItalic> may be specified using the following syntax:</para>
        <para>
          <command>{#<replaceable>identifier</replaceable> .<replaceable>class1</replaceable> .<replaceable>class2</replaceable>&#160;<replaceable>name1</replaceable>="<replaceable>value1</replaceable>" <replaceable>name2</replaceable>="<replaceable>value2</replaceable>" ...}</command>
        </para>
        <para>The following attributes are defined:</para>
      </content>
      <sections>
        <section address="">
          <title>
            <legacyItalic>
              <codeInline>identifier</codeInline>
            </legacyItalic>
          </title>
          <content>
            <list class="nobullet">
              <listItem>
                <para>a string value used for resolving local links to the section.
If no value is specified, a unique identifier will be assigned based on the header text; detailed algorithm TBD.</para>
              </listItem>
            </list>
          </content>
        </section>
        <section address="">
          <title>
            <legacyItalic>
              <codeInline>class</codeInline>
            </legacyItalic>
          </title>
          <content>
            <list class="nobullet">
              <listItem>
                <para>Ignored.</para>
              </listItem>
            </list>
          </content>
        </section>
        <section address="autoOutline">
          <title>
            <codeInline>autoOutline</codeInline>
          </title>
          <content>
            <list class="nobullet">
              <listItem>
                <para>a Boolean value indicating whether an automatic section outline should be generated.
If no attribute value is specified, a section outline <legacyItalic>should</legacyItalic> be generated for a section with an setex-style header,
and <legacyItalic>should not</legacyItalic> be generated for a section with an ATX-style header.</para>
              </listItem>
            </list>
          </content>
        </section>
        <section address="outlineDepth">
          <title>
            <codeInline>outlineDepth</codeInline>
          </title>
          <content>
            <list class="nobullet">
              <listItem>
                <para>an integer value indicating the maximum depth of the automatic section outline, if one is generated.
If no attribute value is specified, a zero-depth outline <legacyItalic>should</legacyItalic> be generated.</para>
              </listItem>
            </list>
          </content>
        </section>
        <section address="outlineLead">
          <title>
            <codeInline>outlineLead</codeInline>
          </title>
          <content>
            <list class="nobullet">
              <listItem>
                <para>a string value that will be used as the lead-in text rendered before the automatic outline, if one is generated.
If an empty string is specified, the lead-in text <legacyItalic>should</legacyItalic> be omitted.
If no attribute value is specified, a default lead-in text <legacyItalic>may</legacyItalic> be used.</para>
              </listItem>
            </list>
          </content>
        </section>
        <section address="noSeeAlso">
          <title>
            <codeInline>noSeeAlso</codeInline>
          </title>
          <content>
            <list class="nobullet">
              <listItem>
                <para>a Boolean value indicating whether the <legacyItalic>See Also</legacyItalic> sub-section will be excluded from the automatic section outline, if both are generated.
If no attribute value is specified, the <legacyItalic>See Also</legacyItalic> sub-section <legacyItalic>should</legacyItalic> be excluded if it has an ATX-style header,
and <legacyItalic>shoud not</legacyItalic> be excluded if it has a setext-style header.</para>
              </listItem>
            </list>
          </content>
        </section>
      </sections>
    </section>
